	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Polokwane – The headless body of a middle-aged woman from Lulekani, outside Phalaborwa, was found in her bedroom on Monday in what police suspect may be a ritual killing. Family members found the woman's body in the early hours of the morning, according to police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe. "The motive behind this incident is still unknown, but ritual killing may not be ruled out," said Ngoepe. ALSO READ: Charred remains found in car at Cape Town station not yet identified Police are still looking for the woman's head. The deceased's two younger brothers were brought in for questioning by police but no suspects have been arrested. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  